 from Paper 3 also informs our regularization strategy—interpreting diversity constraints as a form of controlled perturbation akin to privacy-preserving noise, but tuned to enhance rather than degrade group-level robustness. This leads to a unified optimization framework with formal guarantees on both performance deviation and behavioral spread.

